{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_37400c1f4a4a40b1b1866038","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# About Ansible Molecule\n2\t\n3\t[![PyPI Package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/molecule)](https://pypi.org/project/molecule/)\n4\t[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/molecule/badge/?version=latest)](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule/)\n5\t[![image](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/workflows/tox/badge.svg)](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/actions)\n6\t[![Python Black Code Style](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg)](https://github.com/python/black)\n7\t[![Ansible Code of Conduct](https://img.shields.io/badge/Code%20of%20Conduct-silver.svg)](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/latest/community/code_of_conduct.html)\n8\t[![Discussions](https://img.shields.io/badge/Discussions-silver.svg)](https://forum.ansible.com/tag/molecule)\n9\t[![Repository License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-brightgreen.svg)](LICENSE)\n10\t\n11\tMolecule is an Ansible testing framework designed for developing and testing\n12\t[Ansible](https://ansible.com) collections, playbooks, and roles.\n13\t\n14\tMolecule leverages standard Ansible features including inventory, playbooks,\n15\tand collections to provide flexible testing workflows. Test scenarios can\n16\ttarget any system or service reachable from Ansible, from containers and\n17\tvirtual machines to cloud infrastructure, hyperscaler services, APIs,\n18\tdatabases, and network devices. Molecule can also validate inventory\n19\tconfigurations and dynamic inventory sources.\n20\t\n21\tMolecule encourages an approach that results in consistently developed\n22\tAnsible content that is well-written, easily understood and maintained.\n23\t\n24\tMolecule supports only the latest two major versions of Ansible (N/N-1).\n25\t\n26\tOnce installed, the command line can be called using any of the methods\n27\tbelow:\n28\t\n29\t```bash\n30\tmolecule ...\n31\tpython3 -m molecule ...  # python module calling method\n32\t```\n33\t\n34\t## Documentation\n35\t\n36\tRead the documentation and more at <https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule//>.\n37\t\n38\t## Get Involved\n39\t\n40\tSee the [Talk to us](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule//contributing/#talk-to-us) section of the documentation to ask questions, find help, and join the conversation.\n41\t\n42\tFor complete details, see the\n43\t[Ansible communication guide](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/devel/community/communication.html).\n44\t\n45\tIf you want to get moving fast and make a quick patch:\n46\t\n47\t```bash\n48\tgit clone https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule && cd molecule\n49\tpython3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate\n50\tpython3 -m pip install -U setuptools pip tox\n51\t```\n52\t\n53\tAnd you're ready to make your changes!\n54\t\n55\t## Authors\n56\t\n57\tMolecule project was created by [Retr0h](https://github.com/retr0h) and\n58\tit is now community-maintained as part of the\n59\t[Ansible](https://ansible.com) by Red Hat project.\n60\t\n61\t## License\n62\t\n63\tThe\n64\t[MIT](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/blob/main/LICENSE)\n65\tLicense.\n66\t\n67\tThe logo is licensed under the [Creative Commons NoDerivatives 4.0\n68\tLicense](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0/).\n69\t\n70\tIf you have some other use in mind, contact us.\n71\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8f1a6dd-da89-40cc-8d6b-5f3103d147f5","uuid":"8187a0ba-d1bb-4032-a1a0-1887fddf76bb","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:37:24.182Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md","content":"# About Ansible Molecule\n\n[![PyPI Package](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/molecule)](https://pypi.org/project/molecule/)\n[![Documentation Status](https://readthedocs.org/projects/molecule/badge/?version=latest)](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule/)\n[![image](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/workflows/tox/badge.svg)](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/actions)\n[![Python Black Code Style](https://img.shields.io/badge/code%20style-black-000000.svg)](https://github.com/python/black)\n[![Ansible Code of Conduct](https://img.shields.io/badge/Code%20of%20Conduct-silver.svg)](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/latest/community/code_of_conduct.html)\n[![Discussions](https://img.shields.io/badge/Discussions-silver.svg)](https://forum.ansible.com/tag/molecule)\n[![Repository License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-brightgreen.svg)](LICENSE)\n\nMolecule is an Ansible testing framework designed for developing and testing\n[Ansible](https://ansible.com) collections, playbooks, and roles.\n\nMolecule leverages standard Ansible features including inventory, playbooks,\nand collections to provide flexible testing workflows. Test scenarios can\ntarget any system or service reachable from Ansible, from containers and\nvirtual machines to cloud infrastructure, hyperscaler services, APIs,\ndatabases, and network devices. Molecule can also validate inventory\nconfigurations and dynamic inventory sources.\n\nMolecule encourages an approach that results in consistently developed\nAnsible content that is well-written, easily understood and maintained.\n\nMolecule supports only the latest two major versions of Ansible (N/N-1).\n\nOnce installed, the command line can be called using any of the methods\nbelow:\n\n```bash\nmolecule ...\npython3 -m molecule ...  # python module calling method\n```\n\n## Documentation\n\nRead the documentation and more at <https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule//>.\n\n## Get Involved\n\nSee the [Talk to us](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule//contributing/#talk-to-us) section of the documentation to ask questions, find help, and join the conversation.\n\nFor complete details, see the\n[Ansible communication guide](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/devel/community/communication.html).\n\nIf you want to get moving fast and make a quick patch:\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule && cd molecule\npython3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate\npython3 -m pip install -U setuptools pip tox\n```\n\nAnd you're ready to make your changes!\n\n## Authors\n\nMolecule project was created by [Retr0h](https://github.com/retr0h) and\nit is now community-maintained as part of the\n[Ansible](https://ansible.com) by Red Hat project.\n\n## License\n\nThe\n[MIT](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/blob/main/LICENSE)\nLicense.\n\nThe logo is licensed under the [Creative Commons NoDerivatives 4.0\nLicense](https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0/).\n\nIf you have some other use in mind, contact us.\n","numLines":71,"startLine":1,"totalLines":71}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_e174d109654841ccb38c654f","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t[project]\n2\tname = \"molecule\"\n3\tdescription = \"Molecule aids in the development and testing of Ansible roles\"\n4\treadme = \"README.md\"\n5\trequires-python = \">=3.10\"\n6\tlicense = \"MIT\"\n7\tauthors = [{ \"name\" = \"Ansible by Red Hat\", \"email\" = \"info@ansible.com\" }]\n8\tmaintainers = [{ \"name\" = \"Ansible by Red Hat\", \"email\" = \"info@ansible.com\" }]\n9\tkeywords = [\"ansible\", \"molecule\", \"roles\", \"testing\"]\n10\tclassifiers = [\n11\t  \"Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable\",\n12\t  \"Environment :: Console\",\n13\t  \"Intended Audience :: Developers\",\n14\t  \"Intended Audience :: Information Technology\",\n15\t  \"Intended Audience :: System Administrators\",\n16\t  \"Operating System :: MacOS\",\n17\t  \"Operating System :: POSIX\",\n18\t  \"Programming Language :: Python\",\n19\t  \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3\",\n20\t  \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10\",\n21\t  \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11\",\n22\t  \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12\",\n23\t  \"Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13\",\n24\t  \"Topic :: Software Development :: Bug Tracking\",\n25\t  \"Topic :: Software Development :: Quality Assurance\",\n26\t  \"Topic :: Software Development :: Testing\",\n27\t  \"Topic :: System :: Systems Administration\",\n28\t  \"Topic :: Utilities\",\n29\t]\n30\tdependencies = [\n31\t  \"ansible-compat>=25.1.4\",\n32\t  \"ansible-core>=2.15.0\",\n33\t  \"click>=8.0,<9\",\n34\t  \"enrich>=1.2.7\",\n35\t  \"jinja2>=2.11.3\",\n36\t  \"jsonschema>=4.9.1\",\n37\t  \"packaging>=23.2\",\n38\t  \"pluggy>=0.7.1,<2.0\",\n39\t  \"pyyaml>=5.1\",\n40\t  \"rich>=9.5.1\",\n41\t  \"wcmatch>=8.1.2\",\n42\t]\n43\tdynamic = [\"version\"]\n44\t\n45\t[project.urls]\n46\tchangelog = \"https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/releases\"\n47\tdocumentation = \"https://docs.ansible.com/projects/molecule/\"\n48\thomepage = \"https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule\"\n49\trepository = \"https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule\"\n50\t\n51\t[project.scripts]\n52\tmolecule = \"molecule.__main__:main\"\n53\t\n54\t[project.entry-points.\"molecule.driver\"]\n55\tdefault = \"molecule.driver.delegated:Delegated\"\n56\t\n57\t[project.entry-points.\"molecule.verifier\"]\n58\tansible = \"molecule.verifier.ansible:Ansible\"\n59\ttestinfra = \"molecule.verifier.testinfra:Testinfra\"\n60\t\n61\t[dependency-groups]\n62\tdev = [\n63\t  \"ansi2html>=1.8.0\",\n64\t  \"ansible-navigator>=25.8.0\",\n65\t  \"coverage[toml]>=7.10.6\",\n66\t  \"docker>=7.1.0\",\n67\t  \"filelock>=3.9.0\",\n68\t  \"pexpect>=4.9.0,<5\",\n69\t  \"pytest>=9\",\n70\t  \"pytest-instafail>=0.5.0\",\n71\t  \"pytest-mock>=3.10.0\",\n72\t  \"pytest-plus>=0.7.0\",\n73\t  \"pytest-xdist>=3.8.0\",\n74\t  \"requests!=2.32.0\",\n75\t  \"tox>=4.46.0\",\n76\t  \"types-jsonschema>=4.25.1.20250822\",\n77\t  \"types-pexpect>=4.9.0.20250809\",\n78\t  \"types-pyyaml>=6.0.12.20250822\",\n79\t]\n80\tcollection = [\n81\t  \"molecule>=6.0.0\",\n82\t  \"pip>=2.20.3\",\n83\t  \"pytest-ansible>=26.2.0\",\n84\t  \"tox>=4.46.0\",\n85\t  \"tox-ansible>=26.2.1\",\n86\t  \"tox-extra>=2.2.0\",\n87\t  \"tox-uv>=1.32.1\"\n88\t]\n89\tdocs = [\"linkchecker>=10.4.0\", \"mkdocs-ansible>=24.3.0\"]\n90\tlint = [\n91\t  \"ansible-lint>=6.12.1\",\n92\t  \"codespell>=2.4.1\",\n93\t  \"mypy>=1.17.1\",\n94\t  \"pip>=25.2\",\n95\t  \"prek>=0.3.3\",\n96\t  \"pydoclint>=0.7.1\",\n97\t  \"pylint>=3.3.8\",\n98\t  \"pytest>=9\",\n99\t  \"ruff>=0.12.11\",\n100\t  \"setuptools>=51.1.1\",\n101\t  \"tombi>=0.7.32\",\n102\t]\n103\tpkg = [\"build>=0.9\", \"pip>=25.2\", \"pipx>=1.7.1\", \"twine>=4.0.2\"]\n104\t\n105\t[build-system]\n106\trequires = [\n107\t  \"setuptools_scm[toml] >= 7.0.5\",  # required for \"no-local-version\" scheme\n108\t  \"setuptools >= 65.3.0\",  # required by pyproject+setuptools_scm integration and editable installs\n109\t]\n110\tbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n111\t\n112\t[tool.codespell]\n113\tignore-words-list = \"indention\"\n114\tskip = \".cache,.yarn,dist,node_modules,.mypy_cache,.ruff_cache,site,.git,dictionary.txt,.venv,media,.ansible,_readthedocs,uv.lock\"\n115\t\n116\t[tool.coverage.report]\n117\texclude_also = [\"if TYPE_CHECKING:\", \"pragma: no cover\"]\n118\tfail_under = 89\n119\tignore_errors = false  # avoid spamming the console if there are no errors\n120\tshow_missing = true\n121\tskip_covered = true\n122\tskip_empty = true\n123\t\n124\t[tool.coverage.run]\n125\t# branch is more reliable than lines, protects against false positives\n126\tbranch = true\n127\tconcurrency = [\"multiprocessing\", \"thread\"]\n128\tomit = [\"types.py\", \"_version.py\"]\n129\tparallel = true\n130\trelative_files = true\n131\tsource = [\"src\"]\n132\t\n133\t[tool.mypy]\n134\tcache_dir = \"./.cache/.mypy\"\n135\t# To ensure that calling `mypy .` produces desired results (vscode)\n136\texclude = [\"build\"]\n137\tfiles = [\"src\", \"tests\"]\n138\tpython_version = \"3.10\"\n139\tstrict = true\n140\t\n141\t[[tool.mypy.overrides]]\n142\tignore_missing_imports = true\n143\tmodule = [\n144\t  \"testinfra.*\",  # https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest-testinfra/issues/619\n145\t]\n146\t\n147\t[tool.pydoclint]\n148\tallow-init-docstring = true\n149\targ-type-hints-in-docstring = false\n150\tbaseline = \".config/pydoclint-baseline.txt\"\n151\tcheck-return-types = false\n152\tcheck-yield-types = false\n153\texclude = '\\.ansible|\\.cache|\\.git|\\.tox|build|out|venv'\n154\tquiet = true  # no need to print out the files being checked\n155\tshould-document-private-class-attributes = true\n156\tshow-filenames-in-every-violation-message = true\n157\tskip-checking-short-docstrings = false\n158\tstyle = \"google\"\n159\t\n160\t[tool.pylint]\n161\t[tool.pylint.format]\n162\tmax-line-length = 100\n163\t\n164\t[tool.pylint.master]\n165\tgood-names = \"i,j,k,ex,Run,_,f,fh\"\n166\tignore = [\n167\t  \"_version.py\",  # built by setuptools_scm\n168\t]\n169\tjobs = 0\n170\tno-docstring-rgx = \"__.*__\"\n171\t\n172\t[tool.pylint.messages_control]\n173\tdisable = [\n174\t  \"unknown-option-value\",\n175\t  \"R0401\",  # cyclic-import — lazy imports in base.py -> worker.py are intentional\n176\t  # https://gist.github.com/cidrblock/ec3412bacfeb34dbc2d334c1d53bef83\n177\t  \"C0103\",  # invalid-name / ruff N815\n178\t  \"C0105\",  # typevar-name-incorrect-variance / ruff PLC0105\n179\t  \"C0112\",  # empty-docstring / ruff D419\n180\t  \"C0113\",  # unneeded-not / ruff SIM208\n181\t  \"C0114\",  # missing-module-docstring / ruff D100\n182\t  \"C0115\",  # missing-class-docstring / ruff D101\n183\t  \"C0116\",  # missing-function-docstring / ruff D103\n184\t  \"C0121\",  # singleton-comparison / ruff PLC0121\n185\t  \"C0123\",  # unidiomatic-typecheck / ruff E721\n186\t  \"C0131\",  # typevar-double-variance / ruff PLC0131\n187\t  \"C0132\",  # typevar-name-mismatch / ruff PLC0132\n188\t  \"C0198\",  # bad-docstring-quotes / ruff Q002\n189\t  \"C0199\",  # docstring-first-line-empty / ruff D210\n190\t  \"C0201\",  # consider-iterating-dictionary / ruff SIM118\n191\t  \"C0202\",  # bad-classmethod-argument / ruff PLC0202\n192\t  \"C0205\",  # single-string-used-for-slots / ruff PLC0205\n193\t  \"C0208\",  # use-sequence-for-iteration / ruff PLC0208\n194\t  \"C0301\",  # line-too-long / ruff E501\n195\t  \"C0303\",  # trailing-whitespace / ruff W291\n196\t  \"C0304\",  # missing-final-newline / ruff W292\n197\t  \"C0321\",  # multiple-statements / ruff PLC0321\n198\t  \"C0410\",  # multiple-imports / ruff E401\n199\t  \"C0411\",  # wrong-import-order / ruff I001\n200\t  \"C0412\",  # ungrouped-imports / ruff I001\n201\t  \"C0413\",  # wrong-import-position / ruff E402\n202\t  \"C0414\",  # useless-import-alias / ruff PLC0414\n203\t  \"C0415\",  # import-outside-toplevel / ruff PLC0415\n204\t  \"C0501\",  # consider-using-any-or-all / ruff PLC0501\n205\t 