{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_86ea7b915a304b86afacec59","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tci:\n3\t  # We rely on renovate to update it but there is no way to fully disable it\n4\t  # https://github.com/pre-commit-ci/issues/issues/83\n5\t  autoupdate_schedule: quarterly\n6\t  skip:\n7\t    - codecov\n8\t    - codespell # missing uv\n9\t    - cspell\n10\t    - md # missing uv\n11\t    - mypy # missing uv\n12\t    - ruff # missing uv\n13\t    - shellcheck # missing uv\n14\t    - toml # missing uv\n15\t    - yamllint # missing uv\n16\t\n17\tdefault_language_version:\n18\t  # minimal version we support officially as this will impact mypy, pylint\n19\t  # minimal version determined by minimal version required by ansible-core, but\n20\t  # we might keep a backwards compatibility version for older ones\n21\t  python: \"3.11\"\n22\trepos:\n23\t  - repo: meta\n24\t    hooks:\n25\t      - id: check-useless-excludes\n26\t  - repo: https://github.com/ansible/actions\n27\t    rev: v0.5.1\n28\t    hooks:\n29\t      - id: toml\n30\t        priority: 0\n31\t      - id: mypy\n32\t        priority: 1\n33\t      - id: ruff\n34\t        priority: 0\n35\t      - id: codespell\n36\t        priority: 1\n37\t      - id: cspell\n38\t        priority: 0\n39\t      - id: yamllint\n40\t        priority: 0\n41\t      - id: md\n42\t        priority: 0\n43\t      - id: codecov\n44\t        priority: 0\n45\t      - id: shellcheck\n46\t        priority: 0\n47\t  - repo: https://github.com/astral-sh/uv-pre-commit\n48\t    rev: 0.10.7\n49\t\n50\t    hooks:\n51\t      - id: uv-sync\n52\t      - id: uv-lock\n53\t      - id: uv-lock\n54\t        name: \"deps: upgrade via uv sync --upgrade\"\n55\t        alias: deps\n56\t        args: [\"--upgrade\"]\n57\t        stages: [manual]\n58\t  - repo: https://github.com/biomejs/pre-commit\n59\t    rev: \"v2.4.4\"\n60\t    hooks:\n61\t      - id: biome-check\n62\t        name: biome\n63\t        alias: biome\n64\t        args: [--unsafe]\n65\t        priority: 0\n66\t  - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks.git\n67\t    rev: v6.0.0\n68\t    hooks:\n69\t      - id: check-added-large-files\n70\t      - id: check-merge-conflict\n71\t      - id: check-symlinks\n72\t      - id: debug-statements\n73\t      - id: detect-private-key\n74\t      - id: end-of-file-fixer\n75\t      - id: trailing-whitespace\n76\t\n77\t  - repo: https://github.com/rhysd/actionlint\n78\t    rev: v1.7.11\n79\t    hooks:\n80\t      - id: actionlint\n81\t        priority: 0\n82\t\n83\t  - repo: https://github.com/jsh9/pydoclint\n84\t    rev: \"0.8.3\"\n85\t    hooks:\n86\t      - id: pydoclint\n87\t        # This allows automatic reduction of the baseline file when needed.\n88\t        entry: sh -ec \"pydoclint . && pydoclint --generate-baseline=1 .\"\n89\t        pass_filenames: false\n90\t        priority: 1\n91\t\n92\t  - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/pylint.git\n93\t    rev: v4.0.5\n94\t    hooks:\n95\t      - id: pylint\n96\t        priority: 1\n97\t        args:\n98\t          - --output-format=colorized\n99\t        additional_dependencies:\n100\t          - ansible-compat>=25.1.4\n101\t          - click\n102\t          - click-help-colors\n103\t          - enrich>=1.2.7\n104\t          - filelock\n105\t          - jsonschema\n106\t          - pexpect\n107\t          - pytest-mock\n108\t          - pytest-testinfra\n109\t          - wcmatch\n110\t\n111\t  - repo: https://github.com/ansible/ansible-lint\n112\t    rev: v26.2.0\n113\t    hooks:\n114\t      - id: ansible-lint\n115\t        stages: [manual]\n116\t  - repo: https://github.com/ansible/team-devtools\n117\t    rev: v26.2.0\n118\t    hooks:\n119\t      - id: check-platform-constraints\n120\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8f1a6dd-da89-40cc-8d6b-5f3103d147f5","uuid":"89116b90-7a1b-420b-a172-3b27288130d4","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:37:33.659Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/.pre-commit-config.yaml","content":"---\nci:\n  # We rely on renovate to update it but there is no way to fully disable it\n  # https://github.com/pre-commit-ci/issues/issues/83\n  autoupdate_schedule: quarterly\n  skip:\n    - codecov\n    - codespell # missing uv\n    - cspell\n    - md # missing uv\n    - mypy # missing uv\n    - ruff # missing uv\n    - shellcheck # missing uv\n    - toml # missing uv\n    - yamllint # missing uv\n\ndefault_language_version:\n  # minimal version we support officially as this will impact mypy, pylint\n  # minimal version determined by minimal version required by ansible-core, but\n  # we might keep a backwards compatibility version for older ones\n  python: \"3.11\"\nrepos:\n  - repo: meta\n    hooks:\n      - id: check-useless-excludes\n  - repo: https://github.com/ansible/actions\n    rev: v0.5.1\n    hooks:\n      - id: toml\n        priority: 0\n      - id: mypy\n        priority: 1\n      - id: ruff\n        priority: 0\n      - id: codespell\n        priority: 1\n      - id: cspell\n        priority: 0\n      - id: yamllint\n        priority: 0\n      - id: md\n        priority: 0\n      - id: codecov\n        priority: 0\n      - id: shellcheck\n        priority: 0\n  - repo: https://github.com/astral-sh/uv-pre-commit\n    rev: 0.10.7\n\n    hooks:\n      - id: uv-sync\n      - id: uv-lock\n      - id: uv-lock\n        name: \"deps: upgrade via uv sync --upgrade\"\n        alias: deps\n        args: [\"--upgrade\"]\n        stages: [manual]\n  - repo: https://github.com/biomejs/pre-commit\n    rev: \"v2.4.4\"\n    hooks:\n      - id: biome-check\n        name: biome\n        alias: biome\n        args: [--unsafe]\n        priority: 0\n  - repo: https://github.com/pre-commit/pre-commit-hooks.git\n    rev: v6.0.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: check-added-large-files\n      - id: check-merge-conflict\n      - id: check-symlinks\n      - id: debug-statements\n      - id: detect-private-key\n      - id: end-of-file-fixer\n      - id: trailing-whitespace\n\n  - repo: https://github.com/rhysd/actionlint\n    rev: v1.7.11\n    hooks:\n      - id: actionlint\n        priority: 0\n\n  - repo: https://github.com/jsh9/pydoclint\n    rev: \"0.8.3\"\n    hooks:\n      - id: pydoclint\n        # This allows automatic reduction of the baseline file when needed.\n        entry: sh -ec \"pydoclint . && pydoclint --generate-baseline=1 .\"\n        pass_filenames: false\n        priority: 1\n\n  - repo: https://github.com/pycqa/pylint.git\n    rev: v4.0.5\n    hooks:\n      - id: pylint\n        priority: 1\n        args:\n          - --output-format=colorized\n        additional_dependencies:\n          - ansible-compat>=25.1.4\n          - click\n          - click-help-colors\n          - enrich>=1.2.7\n          - filelock\n          - jsonschema\n          - pexpect\n          - pytest-mock\n          - pytest-testinfra\n          - wcmatch\n\n  - repo: https://github.com/ansible/ansible-lint\n    rev: v26.2.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: ansible-lint\n        stages: [manual]\n  - repo: https://github.com/ansible/team-devtools\n    rev: v26.2.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: check-platform-constraints\n","numLines":120,"startLine":1,"totalLines":120}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_3ccd7b008bec4d3696d11a6e","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Contributing\n2\t\n3\tNoticed a bug or have an idea to improve Ansible Molecule?\n4\tWant to write some documentation or share your expertise on the forum?\n5\tThere are many ways to get involved and contribute, find out how.\n6\t\n7\t## Guidelines\n8\t\n9\t- We are interested in various different kinds of improvement for\n10\t  Molecule; please feel free to raise an\n11\t  [Issue](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/issues/new/choose)\n12\t  if you would like to work on something major to ensure efficient\n13\t  collaboration and avoid duplicate effort.\n14\t- Create a topic branch from where you want to base your work.\n15\t- Make sure you have added tests for your changes.\n16\t- Although not required, it is good to sign off commits using\n17\t  `git commit --signoff`, and agree that usage of `--signoff`\n18\t  constitutes agreement with the terms of [DCO\n19\t  1.1](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/blob/main/DCO_1_1.md).\n20\t- Run all the tests to ensure nothing else was accidentally broken.\n21\t- Reformat the code by following the formatting section below.\n22\t- Submit a pull request.\n23\t\n24\t## Talk to us\n25\t\n26\tConnect with the Ansible community!\n27\t\n28\tJoin the Ansible forum to ask questions, get help, and interact with the\n29\tcommunity.\n30\t\n31\t- [Get Help](https://forum.ansible.com/c/help/6): get help or help others.\n32\t  Please add appropriate tags if you start new discussions, for example use the\n33\t  `molecule`, `molecule6`, or `devtools` tags.\n34\t- [Social Spaces](https://forum.ansible.com/c/chat/4): meet and interact with\n35\t  fellow enthusiasts.\n36\t- [News & Announcements](https://forum.ansible.com/c/news/5): track project-wide\n37\t  announcements including social events.\n38\t\n39\tTo get release announcements and important changes from the community, see the\n40\t[Bullhorn newsletter](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/devel/community/communication.html#the-bullhorn).\n41\t\n42\tYou can find more information in the\n43\t[Ansible communication guide](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/devel/community/communication.html).\n44\t\n45\tPossible security bugs should be reported via email to\n46\t<mailto:security@ansible.com>.\n47\t\n48\t## Code Of Conduct\n49\t\n50\tPlease see our [Code of\n51\tConduct](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/blob/main/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\n52\tdocument.\n53\t\n54\t## Pull Request and Governance\n55\t\n56\t- If your PRs get stuck [join us on\n57\t  IRC](https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/Molecule#join-the-discussion)\n58\t  or add to the [working group\n59\t  agenda](https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/Molecule#meetings).\n60\t- The code style is what is enforced by CI, everything else is\n61\t  off-topic.\n62\t- All PRs must be reviewed by one other person. This is enforced by\n63\t  GitHub. Larger changes require +2.\n64\t\n65\t## Testing\n66\t\n67\tMolecule has an extensive set of unit and functional tests. Molecule\n68\tuses [Tox](https://tox.wiki/en/latest/) factors to generate a\n69\tmatrix of python x Ansible x unit/functional tests. Manual setup\n70\trequired as of this time.\n71\t\n72\t### Dependencies\n73\t\n74\tTests will be skipped when the driver's binary is not present.\n75\t\n76\tInstall the test framework [Tox](https://tox.wiki/en/latest/).\n77\t\n78\t```bash\n79\tpython3 -m pip install tox\n80\t```\n81\t\n82\t### Running the test suite\n83\t\n84\tRun all tests, including linting and coverage reports. This should be\n85\trun prior to merging or submitting a pull request.\n86\t\n87\t```bash\n88\ttox\n89\t```\n90\t\n91\t### List available scenarios\n92\t\n93\tList all available scenarios. This is useful to target specific Python\n94\tand Ansible version for the functional and unit tests.\n95\t\n96\t```bash\n97\ttox -av\n98\t```\n99\t\n100\t### Unit\n101\t\n102\tRun all unit tests with coverage.\n103\t\n104\t```bash\n105\ttox -e py\n106\t```\n107\t\n108\tRun all unit tests for a specific version of Python.\n109\t\n110\t```bash\n111\ttox -e py311\n112\t```\n113\t\n114\t### Linting\n115\t\n116\tLinting is performed by a combination of linters.\n117\t\n118\tRun all the linters (some perform changes to conform the code to the\n119\tstyle rules).\n120\t\n121\t```bash\n122\ttox -e lint\n123\t```\n124\t\n125\t### Documentation\n126\t\n127\tGenerate the documentation, using [mkdocs](https://www.mkdocs.org/).\n128\t\n129\t```bash\n130\ttox -e docs\n131\t```\n132\t\n133\t### Updating Dependencies\n134\t\n135\tDependencies need to be updated by hand in:\n136\t\n137\t- `.config/requirements.in`\n138\t- `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (2 places)\n139\t\n140\t## Credits\n141\t\n142\tBased on the good work of John Dewey\n143\t([\\@retr0h](https://github.com/retr0h)) and other\n144\t[contributors](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/graphs/contributors).\n145\tActive member list can be seen at [Molecule working\n146\tgroup](https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/Molecule).\n147\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8f1a6dd-da89-40cc-8d6b-5f3103d147f5","uuid":"52406181-e077-4e70-8010-9816fe38f481","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:37:33.662Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/contributing.md","content":"# Contributing\n\nNoticed a bug or have an idea to improve Ansible Molecule?\nWant to write some documentation or share your expertise on the forum?\nThere are many ways to get involved and contribute, find out how.\n\n## Guidelines\n\n- We are interested in various different kinds of improvement for\n  Molecule; please feel free to raise an\n  [Issue](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/issues/new/choose)\n  if you would like to work on something major to ensure efficient\n  collaboration and avoid duplicate effort.\n- Create a topic branch from where you want to base your work.\n- Make sure you have added tests for your changes.\n- Although not required, it is good to sign off commits using\n  `git commit --signoff`, and agree that usage of `--signoff`\n  constitutes agreement with the terms of [DCO\n  1.1](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/blob/main/DCO_1_1.md).\n- Run all the tests to ensure nothing else was accidentally broken.\n- Reformat the code by following the formatting section below.\n- Submit a pull request.\n\n## Talk to us\n\nConnect with the Ansible community!\n\nJoin the Ansible forum to ask questions, get help, and interact with the\ncommunity.\n\n- [Get Help](https://forum.ansible.com/c/help/6): get help or help others.\n  Please add appropriate tags if you start new discussions, for example use the\n  `molecule`, `molecule6`, or `devtools` tags.\n- [Social Spaces](https://forum.ansible.com/c/chat/4): meet and interact with\n  fellow enthusiasts.\n- [News & Announcements](https://forum.ansible.com/c/news/5): track project-wide\n  announcements including social events.\n\nTo get release announcements and important changes from the community, see the\n[Bullhorn newsletter](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/devel/community/communication.html#the-bullhorn).\n\nYou can find more information in the\n[Ansible communication guide](https://docs.ansible.com/projects/ansible/devel/community/communication.html).\n\nPossible security bugs should be reported via email to\n<mailto:security@ansible.com>.\n\n## Code Of Conduct\n\nPlease see our [Code of\nConduct](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/blob/main/.github/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md)\ndocument.\n\n## Pull Request and Governance\n\n- If your PRs get stuck [join us on\n  IRC](https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/Molecule#join-the-discussion)\n  or add to the [working group\n  agenda](https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/Molecule#meetings).\n- The code style is what is enforced by CI, everything else is\n  off-topic.\n- All PRs must be reviewed by one other person. This is enforced by\n  GitHub. Larger changes require +2.\n\n## Testing\n\nMolecule has an extensive set of unit and functional tests. Molecule\nuses [Tox](https://tox.wiki/en/latest/) factors to generate a\nmatrix of python x Ansible x unit/functional tests. Manual setup\nrequired as of this time.\n\n### Dependencies\n\nTests will be skipped when the driver's binary is not present.\n\nInstall the test framework [Tox](https://tox.wiki/en/latest/).\n\n```bash\npython3 -m pip install tox\n```\n\n### Running the test suite\n\nRun all tests, including linting and coverage reports. This should be\nrun prior to merging or submitting a pull request.\n\n```bash\ntox\n```\n\n### List available scenarios\n\nList all available scenarios. This is useful to target specific Python\nand Ansible version for the functional and unit tests.\n\n```bash\ntox -av\n```\n\n### Unit\n\nRun all unit tests with coverage.\n\n```bash\ntox -e py\n```\n\nRun all unit tests for a specific version of Python.\n\n```bash\ntox -e py311\n```\n\n### Linting\n\nLinting is performed by a combination of linters.\n\nRun all the linters (some perform changes to conform the code to the\nstyle rules).\n\n```bash\ntox -e lint\n```\n\n### Documentation\n\nGenerate the documentation, using [mkdocs](https://www.mkdocs.org/).\n\n```bash\ntox -e docs\n```\n\n### Updating Dependencies\n\nDependencies need to be updated by hand in:\n\n- `.config/requirements.in`\n- `.pre-commit-config.yaml` (2 places)\n\n## Credits\n\nBased on the good work of John Dewey\n([\\@retr0h](https://github.com/retr0h)) and other\n[contributors](https://github.com/ansible-community/molecule/graphs/contributors).\nActive member list can be seen at [Molecule working\ngroup](https://github.com/ansible/community/wiki/Molecule).\n","numLines":147,"startLine":1,"totalLines":147}}}
